  "prompt": "What plans after exam?",
  "response": "Okay, I'm ready to help you brainstorm some post-exam plans! To give you the best ideas, I need a little more information:\n\n1.  **What kind of exam was it?**  Knowing what the exam was for will help narrow down some ideas.\n2.  **Are you looking for relaxation, productivity, or a mix of both?**  Knowing what you want to achieve after your exam will help give you more ideas.\n\n**Here are some general ideas that usually work after a big exam:**\n\n**Relaxation & Recharging:**\n\n*   **Sleep:** Catch up on sleep. \n*   **Relaxing Activities:** Watch movies or TV shows, read a book for pleasure, listen to music, spend time in nature (go for a walk, hike, or visit a park), take a long bath or shower, get a massage.\n*   **Spend Time with Loved Ones:** Connect with family and friends.\n\n**Productivity & Catching Up:**\n\n*   **Catch Up on Chores:** Do laundry, clean your living space, organize things.\n*   **Tackle a Project:** Work on a hobby you've been neglecting, start a creative project (writing, painting, music), or work on a personal project.\n*   **Plan for the Future:** Start thinking about future goals.\n*   **Learn Something New:** Start a new hobby.\n\n**Fun & Social Activities:**\n\n*   **Go Out with Friends:** Celebrate the end of exams with your friends\n*   **Travel:** Plan a short trip.\n*   **Try a New Restaurant or Activity:** Explore new things in your area.\n*   **Attend a Concert or Event:** Enjoy some live entertainment.\n\nOnce you tell me about your exam, I can offer more tailored advice!",
